trans-unit.source: Defines the SOAP fault codes that appear in a SOAP message when an error occurs while communicating with XML Web services using the SOAP version 1.2 protocol.
trans-unit.target: Definierar SOAP-felkoder som visas i ett SOAP-meddelande när det uppstår ett fel vid kommunikation med XML-webbtjänster med SOAP-protokoll version 1.2.

trans-unit.source: A SOAP fault in version 1.2 of the SOAP specification contains a `Code` element and among other things an optional `Subcode` element.
trans-unit.target: Ett SOAP-fel i version 1.2 av SOAP-specifikationen innehåller en `Code` element och bland annat en valfri `Subcode` element.

trans-unit.source: The `Code` element is one of a pre-defined set of codes, informing a recipient that the cause of the error fell into one of five large error categories.
trans-unit.target: Den `Code` element är en av en fördefinierad uppsättning koder, om en mottagare som orsaken till felet har sjunkit ned under en av fem större felkategorier.

trans-unit.source: Those five fault codes are represented by the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.Soap12FaultCodes.ReceiverFaultCode>, <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.Soap12FaultCodes.SenderFaultCode>, <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.Soap12FaultCodes.VersionMismatchFaultCode>, <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.Soap12FaultCodes.MustUnderstandFaultCode>, and <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.Soap12FaultCodes.DataEncodingUnknownFaultCode> fields.
trans-unit.target: De fem felkoderna som representeras av den <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.Soap12FaultCodes.ReceiverFaultCode>, <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.Soap12FaultCodes.SenderFaultCode>, <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.Soap12FaultCodes.VersionMismatchFaultCode>, <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.Soap12FaultCodes.MustUnderstandFaultCode>, och <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.Soap12FaultCodes.DataEncodingUnknownFaultCode>fält.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.Soap12FaultCodes.DataEncodingUnknownFaultCode> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.Soap12FaultCodes.MustUnderstandFaultCode> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.Soap12FaultCodes.VersionMismatchFaultCode> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.Soap12FaultCodes.SenderFaultCode> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.Soap12FaultCodes.ReceiverFaultCode>

trans-unit.source: The `Subcode` element allows the sender of the SOAP fault to provide an application-specific error code.
trans-unit.target: Den `Subcode` -elementet kan avsändaren av SOAP-fel att tillhandahålla en programspecifika felkod.

trans-unit.source: ASP.NET defines two such codes that are represented by the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.Soap12FaultCodes.RpcProcedureNotPresentFaultCode>, <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.Soap12FaultCodes.RpcBadArgumentsFaultCode>, <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.Soap12FaultCodes.EncodingMissingIDFaultCode>, and <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.Soap12FaultCodes.EncodingUntypedValueFaultCode> fields.
trans-unit.target: ASP.NET definierar två koder som representeras av den <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.Soap12FaultCodes.RpcProcedureNotPresentFaultCode>, <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.Soap12FaultCodes.RpcBadArgumentsFaultCode>, <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.Soap12FaultCodes.EncodingMissingIDFaultCode>, och <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.Soap12FaultCodes.EncodingUntypedValueFaultCode>fält.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.Soap12FaultCodes.EncodingUntypedValueFaultCode> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.Soap12FaultCodes.EncodingMissingIDFaultCode> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.Soap12FaultCodes.RpcBadArgumentsFaultCode> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.Soap12FaultCodes.RpcProcedureNotPresentFaultCode>

trans-unit.source: An XML Web service throwing an exception sets the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Code%2A> property, which represents the `Code` element, when a new instance of the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException> or <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapHeaderException> class is created.
trans-unit.target: En XML-webbtjänst som genererar ett undantag anger den <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Code%2A>-egenskap som representerar den `Code` element, när en ny instans av den <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException>eller <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapHeaderException>klassen skapas.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapHeaderException> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Code%2A>

trans-unit.source: That error is transmitted over the wire as a SOAP fault, which a .NET Framework client can catch as a <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException> or <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapHeaderException>.
trans-unit.target: Fel skickas över nätverket som ett SOAP-fel som en .NET Framework-klient kan fånga <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException>eller <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapHeaderException>.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapHeaderException> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException>

trans-unit.source: Represents the SOAP version 1.2 <xref uid="langword_csharp_DataEncodingUnknown" name="DataEncodingUnknown" href=""></xref> fault code indicating the SOAP message is encoded in an unrecognized format.
trans-unit.target: Representerar SOAP version 1.2 <xref uid="langword_csharp_DataEncodingUnknown" name="DataEncodingUnknown" href=""> </xref> felkod som anger SOAP-meddelandet har kodats i ett okänt format.

trans-unit.source: ASP.NET does not automatically throw a <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException> with the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Code%2A> property set to DataEncodingUnknownFaultCode.
trans-unit.target: ASP.NET inte automatiskt utlösa en <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException>med den <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Code%2A>-egenskapen angetts till DataEncodingUnknownFaultCode.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Code%2A> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException>

trans-unit.source: Represents the fault code for missing ID in SOAP encoding data.
trans-unit.target: Representerar felkoden för saknade ID i SOAP-kodning data.

trans-unit.source: Represents the SOAP version 1.2 <xref uid="langword_csharp_enc:UntypedValue" name="enc:UntypedValue" href=""></xref> fault subcode indicating that the SOAP message was RPC-encoded and the type name property of an encoded graph node was not specified.
trans-unit.target: Representerar SOAP version 1.2 <xref uid="langword_csharp_enc:UntypedValue" name="enc:UntypedValue" href=""> </xref> fel delkoden som anger att SOAP-meddelandet var RPC-kodade och typen name-egenskapen för en kodad graph-nod har inte angetts.

trans-unit.source: ASP.NET does not automatically throw a <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException> with the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapFaultSubcode.Code%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property set to EncodingUntypedValueFaultCode.
trans-unit.target: ASP.NET inte automatiskt utlösa en <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException>med den <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapFaultSubcode.Code%2A?displayProperty=fullName>-egenskapen angetts till EncodingUntypedValueFaultCode.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapFaultSubcode.Code%2A?displayProperty=fullName> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException> class has a <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Subcode%2A> property of type <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapFaultSubcode> that represents the SOAP fault subcode.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException>klassen har en <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Subcode%2A>egenskap av typen <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapFaultSubcode>som representerar SOAP-fel delkoden.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapFaultSubcode> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Subcode%2A> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapFaultSubcode.Code%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property represents the URI for the actual SOAP fault subcode.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapFaultSubcode.Code%2A?displayProperty=fullName>egenskap representerar URI för den faktiska SOAP-fel delkoden.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapFaultSubcode.Code%2A?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: When setting the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapFaultSubcode.Code%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property to EncodingUntypedValueFaultCode, set the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Code%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property to <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.Soap12FaultCodes.SenderFaultCode>.
trans-unit.target: När du anger <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapFaultSubcode.Code%2A?displayProperty=fullName>egenskapen till EncodingUntypedValueFaultCode, anger du <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Code%2A?displayProperty=fullName>egenskapen till <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.Soap12FaultCodes.SenderFaultCode>.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.Soap12FaultCodes.SenderFaultCode> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Code%2A?displayProperty=fullName> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapFaultSubcode.Code%2A?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: To be added.
trans-unit.target: Som ska läggas till.

trans-unit.source: Represents the SOAP version 1.2 <xref uid="langword_csharp_MustUnderstand" name="MustUnderstand" href=""></xref> fault code indicating a SOAP header marked with the <xref uid="langword_csharp_MustUnderstand" name="MustUnderstand" href=""></xref> attribute was not processed.
trans-unit.target: Representerar SOAP version 1.2 <xref uid="langword_csharp_MustUnderstand" name="MustUnderstand" href=""> </xref> felkod som indikerar ett SOAP-huvud som markerats med den <xref uid="langword_csharp_MustUnderstand" name="MustUnderstand" href=""> </xref> attributet kunde inte bearbetas.

trans-unit.source: Not all SOAP headers require processing by the recipient.
trans-unit.target: Inte alla SOAP-huvuden kräver bearbetning av mottagaren.

trans-unit.source: However, if a SOAP header is marked with the `MustUnderstand` attribute equal to "true", processing is required.
trans-unit.target: Men om ett SOAP-huvud är markerad med den `MustUnderstand` attribut är lika med värdet "true" bearbetning krävs.

trans-unit.source: Failure to process the header when it resides within a SOAP 1.2 request generates a <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapHeaderException> with the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Code%2A> property set to MustUnderstandFaultCode.
trans-unit.target: Det gick inte att bearbeta huvudet när den befinner sig inom en SOAP 1.2-begäran genererar en <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapHeaderException>med den <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Code%2A>-egenskapen angetts till MustUnderstandFaultCode.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Code%2A> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapHeaderException>

trans-unit.source: If the SOAP request resided within a SOAP 1.1 request, the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Code%2A> property is set to <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.MustUnderstandFaultCode?displayProperty=fullName>.
trans-unit.target: Om SOAP-begäran som fanns i en SOAP 1.1-begäran <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Code%2A>egenskap är inställd på <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.MustUnderstandFaultCode?displayProperty=fullName>.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.MustUnderstandFaultCode?displayProperty=fullName> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Code%2A>

trans-unit.source: Both SOAP 1.1 and 1.2 define `MustUnderstand` SOAP fault codes differing only by the version of the SOAP protocol used to send the SOAP message.
trans-unit.target: Definiera både SOAP 1.1 och 1.2 `MustUnderstand` SOAP-felkoder som skiljer sig bara i versionen av SOAP-protokoll som används för att skicka SOAP-meddelandet.

trans-unit.source: This field represents the SOAP 1.2 version, and the SOAP 1.1 version is represented by <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.MustUnderstandFaultCode?displayProperty=fullName>.
trans-unit.target: Det här fältet motsvarar den SOAP 1.2-versionen och versionen av SOAP 1.1 representeras av <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.MustUnderstandFaultCode?displayProperty=fullName>.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.MustUnderstandFaultCode?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: The two fields map to different qualified names, but you can check whether the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Code%2A> property is either one of the fault codes by calling the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.IsMustUnderstandFaultCode%2A> method.
trans-unit.target: Två fält mappas till olika kvalificerat namn, men du kan kontrollera om den <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Code%2A>egenskapen är någon av felkoderna genom att anropa den <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.IsMustUnderstandFaultCode%2A>metoden.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.IsMustUnderstandFaultCode%2A> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Code%2A>

trans-unit.source: To be added.
trans-unit.target: Som ska läggas till.

trans-unit.source: Represents the SOAP version 1.2 <xref uid="langword_csharp_Receiver" name="Receiver" href=""></xref> fault code indicating an error occurred during the processing of a client call on the server due to a problem with the recipient.
trans-unit.target: Representerar SOAP version 1.2 <xref uid="langword_csharp_Receiver" name="Receiver" href=""> </xref> felkod som indikerar ett fel uppstod under bearbetning av ett klientanrop på servern på grund av ett problem med mottagaren.

trans-unit.source: A <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException> is thrown with the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Code%2A> property set to ReceiverFaultCode when a server is called and it could not respond to a request due to network problems.
trans-unit.target: En <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException>genereras med den <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Code%2A>-egenskapen angetts till ReceiverFaultCode när en server kallas och den kunde inte svara på en begäran på grund av nätverksproblem.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Code%2A> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException>

trans-unit.source: Typically, with this type of exception, the client call may succeed later.
trans-unit.target: Normalt med den här typen av undantag kan klient-anrop lyckas senare.

trans-unit.source: The `Receiver` SOAP fault code is similar to the `Server` fault code, which is represented by the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.ServerFaultCode> field, but the `Server` fault code is used when the SOAP request is sent using SOAP 1.1.
trans-unit.target: Den `Receiver` SOAP felkod liknar den `Server` fault-kod, som representeras av den <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.ServerFaultCode>fält, men `Server` felkod används när SOAP-begäran skickas med SOAP 1.1.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.ServerFaultCode>

trans-unit.source: To check whether the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Code%2A> property is either the `Receiver` or `Server` SOAP fault codes, call the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.IsServerFaultCode%2A> method.
trans-unit.target: Kontrollera om den <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Code%2A>egenskapen är antingen den `Receiver` eller `Server` SOAP felkoder, anropet den <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.IsServerFaultCode%2A>metoden.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.IsServerFaultCode%2A> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Code%2A>

trans-unit.source: To be added.
trans-unit.target: Som ska läggas till.

trans-unit.source: Represents the SOAP version 1.2 <xref uid="langword_csharp_rpc:BadArguments" name="rpc:BadArguments" href=""></xref> fault subcode indicating that arguments sent to the XML Web service method were incorrect or could not be parsed.
trans-unit.target: Representerar SOAP version 1.2 <xref uid="langword_csharp_rpc:BadArguments" name="rpc:BadArguments" href=""> </xref> fel delkoden som indikerar att argument som skickas till den XML-webbtjänstmetoden var felaktig eller kunde inte parsas.

trans-unit.source: ASP.NET does not automatically throw a <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException> with the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapFaultSubcode.Code%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property set to RpcBadArgumentsFaultCode.
trans-unit.target: ASP.NET inte automatiskt utlösa en <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException>med den <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapFaultSubcode.Code%2A?displayProperty=fullName>-egenskapen angetts till RpcBadArgumentsFaultCode.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapFaultSubcode.Code%2A?displayProperty=fullName> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException> class has a <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Subcode%2A> property of type <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapFaultSubcode> that represents the SOAP fault subcode.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException>klassen har en <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Subcode%2A>egenskap av typen <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapFaultSubcode>som representerar SOAP-fel delkoden.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapFaultSubcode> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Subcode%2A> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapFaultSubcode.Code%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property represents the URI for the actual SOAP fault subcode.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapFaultSubcode.Code%2A?displayProperty=fullName>egenskap representerar URI för den faktiska SOAP-fel delkoden.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapFaultSubcode.Code%2A?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: When setting the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapFaultSubcode.Code%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property to RpcBadArgumentsFaultCode, set the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Code%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property to <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.Soap12FaultCodes.SenderFaultCode>.
trans-unit.target: När du anger <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapFaultSubcode.Code%2A?displayProperty=fullName>egenskapen till RpcBadArgumentsFaultCode, anger du <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Code%2A?displayProperty=fullName>egenskapen till <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.Soap12FaultCodes.SenderFaultCode>.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.Soap12FaultCodes.SenderFaultCode> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Code%2A?displayProperty=fullName> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapFaultSubcode.Code%2A?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.target: Som ska läggas till.

trans-unit.target: Representerar SOAP version 1.2 <xref uid="langword_csharp_rpc:ProcedureNotPresent" name="rpc:ProcedureNotPresent" href=""> </xref> fel delkoden som anger XML-webbtjänsten stöder inte den begärda XML webbtjänstmetoden.

trans-unit.source: ASP.NET does not automatically throw a <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException> with the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapFaultSubcode.Code%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property set to RpcProcedureNotPresentFaultCode.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException> class has a <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Subcode%2A> property of type <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapFaultSubcode> that represents the SOAP fault subcode.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException>klassen har en <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Subcode%2A>egenskap av typen <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapFaultSubcode>som representerar SOAP-fel delkoden.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapFaultSubcode> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Subcode%2A> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException>

trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapFaultSubcode.Code%2A?displayProperty=fullName>egenskap representerar URI för den faktiska SOAP-fel delkoden.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapFaultSubcode.Code%2A?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: When setting the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapFaultSubcode.Code%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property to RpcProcedureNotPresentFaultCode, set the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Code%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property to <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.Soap12FaultCodes.SenderFaultCode>.

trans-unit.source: Represents the SOAP version 1.2 <xref uid="langword_csharp_Sender" name="Sender" href=""></xref> fault code indicating a client call was not formatted correctly or did not contain the appropriate information.
trans-unit.target: Representerar SOAP version 1.2 <xref uid="langword_csharp_Sender" name="Sender" href=""> </xref> felkod som indikerar ett klientanrop har inte formaterats korrekt eller innehåller inte rätt information.

trans-unit.source: A <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException> is thrown with the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Code%2A> property set to SenderFaultCode when a SOAP 1.2 request is malformed or a parameter is missing.
trans-unit.target: En <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException>genereras med den <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Code%2A>-egenskapen angetts till SenderFaultCode när en SOAP 1.2-begäran är felaktig eller saknas en parameter.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Code%2A> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException>

trans-unit.source: The `Sender` SOAP fault code is similar to the `Client` fault code, which is represented by the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.ClientFaultCode> field, but the `Client` fault code is used when the SOAP request is sent using SOAP 1.1.
trans-unit.target: Den `Sender` SOAP felkod liknar den `Client` fault-kod, som representeras av den <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.ClientFaultCode>fält, men `Client` felkod används när SOAP-begäran skickas med SOAP 1.1.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.ClientFaultCode>

trans-unit.source: To check whether the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Code%2A> property is either the `Sender` or `Client` SOAP fault codes, call the <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.IsClientFaultCode%2A> method.
trans-unit.target: Kontrollera om den <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Code%2A>egenskapen är antingen den `Sender` eller `Client` SOAP felkoder, anropet den <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.IsClientFaultCode%2A>metoden.</xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.IsClientFaultCode%2A> </xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.SoapException.Code%2A>
